CT of the chest, abdomen and pelvis, including delayed images of the liver, is compared to 10/3/2006, 4/12/2005 and 9/23/1999.
SUMMARY: No definite evidence of metastases from patient's newly-diagnosed colon cancer.
CHEST: Multiple calcified and uncalcified nodules in both lungs (series 2, images 17,25 & 32), some of which appear new since 1999,but the majority of which appear unchanged dating back to 5/27/2001. Fibrotic changes throughout both lungs and architectural distortion in the lung bases has increased since 1999. Postoperative changes of median sternotomy with mechanical aortic valve prosthesis. Thyroid nodules.
ABDOMEN/PELVIS: Bilateral renal cysts, including a left renal cyst that has decreased in size over the last 11 years. No other significant change. Cholecystectomy. Aortoiliac atherosclerotic changes. Moderate enlargement of the prostate gland. Degenerative changes of the thoracolumbar spine and both hips with cystic changes around the left acetabulum.
Hepatic flexure colon cancer
Plan: Laparoscopic-assisted  extended right hemicolectomy.

